<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-136-326 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 795 268</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  June 3 1991 v8 n22 p25(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sony unveils CD ROM multimedia package. (Sony Corp.'s LaserLibrary CD-ROM drive and multimedia software packages) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sony Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Sony Laser Library (CD-ROM drive) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCD-ROMBundled Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Furthering its efforts to make multimedia a household word, Sony Corp.andO;recently introduced the Laser Library, a CD ROM drive bundled with sixmultimedia software titles.andM;Set to debut this summer, the Laser Library includes a CD ROM drive, a set ofhome reference software and headphones, said Sony officials in San Diego.andO;The drive offers digital audio capabilities, letting users play compact disksas well as the multimedia titles, they said.andM;The software titles bundled with Laser Library are: Compton's FamilyEncyclopedia by Compton's Learning Co., a division of Encyclopedia BritannicaInc.; Microsoft Corp.'s Bookshelf Reference Library 1991 Edition; Mammals: AMultimedia Encyclopedia by the National Geographic Society and IBM; Mixed-UpMother Goose by Sierra On-Line Inc.; Languages of the World by NTC PublishingGroup; and The Software Toolworks World Atlas by The Software Toolworks Inc.andM;Sony commands 37 percent of the installed base of CD ROM drives, according tocompany estimates.andP;  The company can be reached at (800) 338-7834.andO;</TEXT></DOC>